main event: A civilian reported a UFO observation in Houma, Louisiana on December 7, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes, The object was described as cigar-shaped, The course of the object was from west to east, There was insufficient data for a scientific evaluation, Tug boat lights were considered as a possible explanation for the sighting.
witness description: civilian, returning home from a scout meeting
